(Pablo Spencer, AP) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Tultepec - The death toll in a fiery wave of blasts at Mexico's largest fireworks market has risen to 35, authorities say as mourners held funerals for people killed in the tragedy.The toll rose as a woman and a child died in hospital, the government of the state of Mexico said.Of the 60 hurt in the explosions in Tultepec outside Mexico City on Tuesday, some remain in critical condition.At the time of the blast the market was packed with customers buying pyrotechnics for traditional year-end festivities.Christmas and New Year parties in many Latin American countries often wrap up with a fireworks free-for-all.The investigation into the cause of the explosions continues.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.